<title>USA: Windmere-Durable settles suit, Q4 shr loss.</title>
<headline>Windmere-Durable settles suit, Q4 shr loss.</headline>
<dateline>MIAMI LAKES, Fla 1997-03-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>Windmere-Durable Holdings Inc on Monday said it had updated its fourth quarter results to a $0.06 per share net loss instead of a $0.12 per share profit after paying $4.5 million to settle a lawsuit by Kabushiki Kaisha Izumi Seiki Seisakusho of Japan.</p>
<p>The suit was filed in April 1994 against Windmere-Durable and David Friedson, its chairman, president and chief executive, the company said. The statement gave no details of the suit and its officials could not immediately be reached for further comment.</p>
<p>    The company said in a release that it would post a charge to net earnings of $3.5 million, or $0.20 per share, for the year ended December 31, 1996, to account for the settlement.</p>
